<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN203-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. cēramāṉ pāḻalūreṟinta neytalaṅkāṉaliḷañcēṭceṉṉiyai ūṉpotipacuṅkuṭaiyār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN203">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kaḻintatu poḻinteṉa vāṉkaṇ māṟiṉun</l>
<l>tollatu viḷainteṉa nilamvaḷaṅ karappiṉu</l>
<l>mellā vuyirkku millāl vāḻkkai</l>
<l>yiṉṉun tammeṉa vemmaṉō rirappiṉ</l>
<l>muṉṉuṅ koṇṭireṉa nummaṉōr maṟutta</l>
<l>liṉṉā tamma viyaṟē raṇṇa</l>
<l>lillatu nirappa lāṟṟā tōriṉu</l>
<l>muḷḷi varunar nacaiyiḻap pōrē</l>
<l>yaṉaiyaiyu mallai nīyē yoṉṉā</l>
<l>rāreyi lavarkaṭ ṭākavu numateṉap</l>
<l>pāṇkaṭa ṉiṟukkum vaḷḷiyōy</l>
<l>pūṇkaṭa ṉentainī yiravalar puravē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>If, because in the past [rain] flew, the clouds changed area, (1)</l>
<l>if because it ripened of old, the soil would hide [its] fertility, (2)</l>
<l>there would be no living for all the beings. (3)</l>
<l>If the likes of us beg “give [us something] yet again”, (4)</l>
<l>the likes of you refusing “you took before” (5)</l>
<l>is unpleasant, ah, majesty with an advancing chariot. (6)</l>
<l>More than those who are not able to fill what is not there (7)</l>
<l>there are those who lose the love for those who come, remembering, (8)</l>
<l>and you are not like that. (9a-c)</l>
<l>You capable of performing [your] duty to bards, (11)</l>
<l>saying “the enemy fortress difficult [to break], being their place is [now] your’s.” (9d-10)</l>
<l>You, father of ornamental virtue, are the protection for supplicants.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
